parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission warning light is illuminated
the vehicle hesitates or stalls when accelerating
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the vehicle shakes or vibrates
the engine RPMs fluctuate
the vehicle is unable to accelerate
the vehicle is stuck in a low gear
the transmission overheats
and the vehicle is unable to move forward or reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to update the PCM can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine and ASC warning lights are illuminated
the vehicle loses motive power
the vehicle is unable to exceed a certain speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, compromising the safety of vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in the event of a crash
despite meeting the deployment criteria; warning lights illuminate on the dashboard indicating airbag system malfunctions; seatbelts fail to lock or function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctions in the airbag system can lead to false warnings, incorrect deployment, or failure to deploy, compromising the safety of vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Airbag warning lights illuminate on the dashboard; airbag system malfunction warnings appear; passenger seatbelt warning lights stay on; airbag system failure to diagnose or repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of seatbelts to lock or function properly can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, compromising the safety of vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Seatbelts fail to lock or function properly; seatbelts do not restrain occupants in the event of a crash; seatbelt warning lights stay on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of a crash, as the seat belt may not properly restrain the occupant.
symptoms: The seat belt is inoperable
the seat belt pretensioner needs to be replaced
the seat belt cover is fractured
the seat belt cannot be retracted
the seat belt becomes loose and does not latch
the seat belt latch becomes stuck
the seat belt rolls up quickly and can cause injury.
